<page>
   <topic>FILE.DRIVE_SPACE_TOTAL Function</topic>
  <description>Returns the number of bytes that can be stored on the drive.</description>   
   
   <syntax>Byte_Count as N = Drive_Space_Total()</syntax>
<arguments>
<argument>
<name>Drive
</name>
<description>The letter of the drive.</description>
</argument></arguments>   
   
   
   
 
   <discussion>
The FILE.DRIVE_SPACE_TOTAL() method returns the size in bytes of Drive.
   </discussion>
 
   <sections>
       <section><title>Example</title>
            <description>Type the following in the Interactive window:</description>
            <example><![CDATA[
file.drive_space_total("c:") -> 5000000000.000000
]]></example>
       </section>
   </sections>
